  "_about": "Eight FailureModes for the discover-project Workflow — one per MUC-001..MUC-008 from .specifications/discover-project/MISUSE_CASES.md. Each FailureMode's description field embeds the verbatim system-response italic string from the corresponding MUC section (one source of truth — the test test_failuremode_user_messages_match_misuse_cases_md enforces byte-equality). Schema: plugins/sulis/brain/compiled/foundation/failuremode.schema.json. Tenant ULID is canonical for the marketplace tenant — sourced from release-train/failuremodes.jsonld _about (derivation: SHA256('tenant-name:sulis-plugins-marketplace') → Crockford base32 with first-char clamp); reused byte-identical. ULIDs come byte-exact from TDD §Canonical Identifiers — FailureMode ULIDs (corrected in commit 2bc3a68).",
  "captured_on": "2026-06-01",

  "failuremodes": [
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM01N0NG1TD1R000000A",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "non-git-directory",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "invalid-input",
      "description": "Founder runs discover-project against a directory that is not a git repository (MUC-001 — UC-004 happy-fail path). The Detect phase's first Step (read-repo-root) calls git rev-parse and on non-zero exit raises this FailureMode. System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-001 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"This directory is not a git repository. discover-project requires a git remote to mint a Project. Run `git init` and add a remote first, or specify `--source-repo <org/name>` explicitly.\" The Workflow MUST exit non-zero with no partial entity persisted to disk.",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Exit non-zero. Surface the exact MUC-001 system response. No retry — founder must address the precondition (run git init + add remote) before re-invoking. Detection lives in the read-repo-root Step which calls git rev-parse --show-toplevel; non-zero exit triggers this FailureMode before any other Step runs. Related NFRs: NFR-004 (safety — no writes outside entity path), NFR-006 (graceful degradation).",
      "expected_frequency": "occasional",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM02CANCE1M1DF10W000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "mid-flow-cancellation",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "other",
      "description": "Founder cancels (Ctrl-C / SIGINT) at any point between session start and write-project-entity Step completion (MUC-002 — UC-005). The Mint phase's atomic-write pattern (write-to-tmp then os.replace) MUST ensure either the full entity persists or nothing does. Any cancellation between tmp.write_text and tmp.replace leaves only the .tmp file behind, which the next discovery run's startup sweep removes (.sulis/projects/*.tmp). Re-running discovery after cancellation MUST be idempotent — same outcome as a first-time run.",
      "recovery_strategy": "compensate",
      "recovery_detail": "Compensation = (a) signal handler catches SIGINT during Mint and unlinks any in-progress .tmp file before terminating; (b) at next session start, the skill sweeps .sulis/projects/*.tmp and removes stale entries. The Project entity is written atomically via os.replace, so a successful Mint is observable as the target file present without a .tmp sibling. Related NFRs: NFR-003 (deterministic re-run), NFR-004 (safety).",
      "expected_frequency": "occasional",
      "blocks_progress": false,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.9
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM03ENT1TYEX1STS0000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "entity-already-exists",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "policy-violation",
      "description": "Founder runs discover-project without --update against a repo where the Project entity already exists at .sulis/projects/<slug>.jsonld (MUC-003 — UC-001/UC-002). System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-003 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"A Project entity already exists at `.sulis/projects/<slug>.jsonld`. To update it, run `/sulis:discover-project --update`. To start fresh, delete the existing file first.\" The Mint phase MUST detect this state in a cheap pre-write check and refuse to overwrite — only the --update flag activates the FR-009 re-discovery diff flow, which is the only safe overwrite path.",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Exit non-zero. Surface the MUC-003 system response. Recovery requires founder to either (a) re-invoke with --update for per-field diff re-discovery (ADR-005), or (b) delete the existing file and re-invoke fresh. No automatic overwrite. Related NFRs: NFR-004 (safety).",
      "expected_frequency": "frequent",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.93
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM041NFERREJECTED000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "inferred-value-rejected",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "business-logic-error",
      "description": "The probabilistic Infer Step proposed a Configuration-Vocabulary value (e.g., deploy_target = github-release) that the founder rejects during the Ask phase (MUC-004 — UC-006). The Ask UI displays: \"Inferred deploy_target = github-release. Confirm or override:\" — the founder types an override; the gather-ambiguous-fields Step records the corrected value before Mint runs. This is not an error condition — it is the structural counter-measure to LLM hallucination (FR-011: no inferred value reaches Mint without explicit consumer confirmation). The Workflow continues normally with the consumer-supplied value replacing the inferred one.",
      "recovery_strategy": "manual-review",
      "recovery_detail": "Founder's override is taken as authoritative. The Mint phase writes the founder-confirmed value, not the inferred one. The signal IS the inference + override pair — logged for future model-drift detection (NFR-003). Related NFRs: NFR-003 (deterministic re-run — founder override survives), NFR-002 (token budget — overrides do not re-invoke the LLM).",
      "expected_frequency": "frequent",
      "blocks_progress": false,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.88
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM05VNKN0WNWFV11D000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "unknown-workflow-ulid",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "business-logic-error",
      "description": "The minted Project entity's release_workflow_ref points at a Workflow ULID that does not resolve to any Workflow the marketplace ships (MUC-005 — UC-001 mint phase). System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-005 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"Project references Workflow `<ulid>` which is not on the marketplace. The mint has been rolled back.\" The Verify phase (FR-008) catches this by invoking the canonical drift detector scoped to the just-minted entity; non-zero drift exit unlinks the target file (the inverse of Step 8's os.replace) and surfaces this FailureMode.",
      "recovery_strategy": "compensate",
      "recovery_detail": "Compensation = roll back the mint by unlinking target_path. The atomic-write pattern from Step 8 (write-to-tmp + os.replace) makes the rollback safe — unlink removes the just-replaced target file leaving the filesystem in the pre-mint state. Founder reviews the drift detector's stderr (surfaced verbatim) to identify why the ULID is unknown — likely a typo in --update path or a marketplace version skew. Related NFRs: NFR-005 (drift visibility).",
      "expected_frequency": "rare",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.9
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM06G1TN0REM0TE00000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "git-no-remote",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "invalid-input",
      "description": "Founder runs discover-project in a git-initialised directory that has no remote configured (MUC-006 — UC-001). The Detect phase's read-repo-root Step distinguishes this substate from MUC-001's not-git state — both arms of the same precondition check. System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-006 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"This repo has no git remote configured. discover-project cannot infer `source.repo`. Either run `git remote add origin <url>`, or specify `--source-repo <org/name>` explicitly to override.\" The Workflow MUST accept --source-repo on the command line (FR-007) so a founder who knows the target can override without setting the remote first.",
      "recovery_strategy": "fallback",
      "recovery_detail": "Two recovery paths: (a) founder runs git remote add origin <url> and re-invokes; (b) founder re-invokes with --source-repo <org/name> override. Without one of those the Workflow MUST NOT proceed — no defaults, no guesses for source.repo. Related NFRs: NFR-006 (graceful degradation).",
      "expected_frequency": "occasional",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.93
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM07M0N0REP0C0110000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "monorepo-sibling-collision",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "policy-violation",
      "description": "Founder runs discover-project in a monorepo root where .sulis/projects/ already contains entities (MUC-007 — UC-003). Without --path scoping, the Detect phase would conflate sibling Projects and the Mint phase could overwrite an existing one. System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-007 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"This repo already has Project entities at `.sulis/projects/`. To mint an additional Project for a sub-path, run `/sulis:discover-project --path <sub-path>`. To update an existing Project, run `/sulis:discover-project --update <slug>`.\" When --path IS specified the Detect phase MUST scope to that sub-path only — no reading manifests or CI outside the scope. The derived slug for the new Project MUST be unique against existing siblings (collision → refuse, same as MUC-003).",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Exit non-zero. Surface the MUC-007 system response. Recovery requires founder to re-invoke with the correct flag (--path for a new sub-Project or --update <slug> for an existing one). Slug collision detection is part of the Mint Step's pre-write check — derived slug compared against existing siblings; collision raises this FailureMode rather than overwriting. Related NFRs: NFR-004 (safety — no writes outside scoped entity path).",
      "expected_frequency": "occasional",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.9
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KT1WFM08TKBDGTEXCEED0000",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "token-budget-exceeded",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "capacity-exceeded",
      "description": "The probabilistic propose-configuration-values Step's LLM call consumed more than the 10000-token budget (MUC-008 — UC-001/UC-002, NFR-002, ADR-006). System response (verbatim from MISUSE_CASES.md MUC-008 — exact text the skill MUST surface): \"Inference exceeded the 10k token budget. Falling back to asking you for all Configuration Vocabulary fields directly.\" The Workflow MUST transition to a degraded Ask phase (NullConfigurationInferrer adapter) that prompts the consumer for every field the Infer Step would have populated — and MUST still produce a valid Project entity at the end. The budget-exceedance signal MUST be logged so the founder can pin a realistic NFR-002 value for v1.1.",
      "recovery_strategy": "fallback",
      "recovery_detail": "Swap LLMConfigurationInferrer for NullConfigurationInferrer for the remainder of this Workflow run. The Null adapter has the same port surface (returns inferences with confidence=0 for every field), which routes every field through the gather-ambiguous-fields Step. Mint proceeds normally with all-founder-supplied values. Log the tokens_consumed counter to the journal for v1.1 budget calibration. Related NFRs: NFR-002 (token budget), NFR-006 (graceful degradation under no-LLM — same fallback path).",
      "expected_frequency": "rare",
      "blocks_progress": false,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.85
    }
  ]
}
